      <hedline>
        <hl1>100 Years of Books</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Lawrence Heyl Jr on Oct 6 special 100th anniversary issue of New York Times Book Review (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In your quotations from reviews that did not meet the test of time (''Oops!''), I note that the only rave is for ''Across the River and Into the Trees.'' You kindly cloak the various reviewers' identities, but I recollect that the admirer who called the declining Hemingway ''the outstanding author since the death of Shakespeare'' was a fellow fiction writer: John O'Hara.</p>
        <p>Lawrence Heyl Jr.  Nyack, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
